* What is Annotation?
➡  it is an extra info which was going to add on ur code.

➡  if u add extra info in ur code ur existing program, files, projects will not be
   affected the feature purpose in which u written the code
   rather then the extra features will be added in this.

➡ It works based on the mechanism of interfaces

➡ That is called Annotation.

* Types of Annotation

                                  Annotation
                                ↙            ↘
                            Build-in       Costume
                          ↙         ↘
  General Purpose Annotations      Meta Annotations
     (java.lang package)      (java.lang.annotation package)
         @Override                    @Inherited
        @Deprecated                   @Documented
       @SafeVar Args                  @Target
     @SuppressWarnings                @Retention
     @FunctionalInterface             @Repeatable


* @ -  it inform complier that this is not a interface, its an annotation type
       which u can add as a suppliment info to ur source code.
* only few interface keywords then it act as a normal interface
* Annotation works on the mechanism of interface

* Categories of Annotations

1. Marker Annotations -  @Override is an example of Marker Annotation.
2. Single value Annotations
3. Full Annotations
4. Type Annotations
5. Repeating Annotations